<div id="review_1908280096" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1908280096" />
    <a title="Jane" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7177008-jane"><img alt="Jane" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1388366904p2/7177008.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1908280096?book_show_action=true">May 01, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jane" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jane" href="/user/show/7177008-jane">Jane</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to Jane by: </span>
      Carol, librarian at Vestal Library
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7177008-jane?shelf=ancient-rome">ancient-rome</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7177008-jane?shelf=library">library</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7177008-jane?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1908280096" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8869219765695874067">One man&apos;s obsession and how it nearly destroys him and his <i>familia</i>. Set in Augustan Rome, this tells of the famous gourmand Apicius , his slave Thrasius, and Apicius&apos; yearning so much for the position as the emperor&apos;s gastronomic advisor that this dream overtakes his life and he sacrifices his daughter to it. Apicius buys Thrasius for his new chef. The two of them love cooking and together develop marvelous dishes. Apicius&apos;s <i>cenae</i> [suppers=banquets] become famous; everyone wants an invitation. T</span>
  <span id="freeText8869219765695874067" style="display:none">One man's obsession and how it nearly destroys him and his <i>familia</i>. Set in Augustan Rome, this tells of the famous gourmand Apicius , his slave Thrasius, and Apicius' yearning so much for the position as the emperor's gastronomic advisor that this dream overtakes his life and he sacrifices his daughter to it. Apicius buys Thrasius for his new chef. The two of them love cooking and together develop marvelous dishes. Apicius's <i>cenae</i> [suppers=banquets] become famous; everyone wants an invitation. Thrasius comes up with the idea for a cookbook, which will make his master's fame through the ages. The enigmatic prophecy of a haruspex is fulfilled: <i>"The more you work for success, the more your sky will darken....For every success, failure will cling to the sides."</i> We follow the joys and tragedies of the characters through a span of years. <br /><br />The author immersed me in that world of sight and taste in this enthralling novel. All the characters, both good and bad, were fully-fleshed. Each part opened with one of the recipes before the story would begin. Descriptions of the luxurious food were amazing. <br /><br />4.5/5. Highly recommended.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8869219765695874067" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


