<div id="review_1957756419" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1957756419" />
    <a title="Emma" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/8575414-emma"><img alt="Emma" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610296277p2/8575414.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1957756419?book_show_action=true">Jun 16, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emma" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emma" href="/user/show/8575414-emma">Emma</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/35009517-feast-of-sorrow">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8575414-emma?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/8575414-emma?shelf=roman-hf">roman-hf</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1957756419" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8109056629345387011">This was just the kind of historical fiction I like. In Roman historical fiction there is a glut of stories based on the army or based on Imperial or Senatorial intrigue.I’ve read quite a few of these and enjoyed them but over time I’ve found they all blend together. Either that, or many retell the same notorious events from different perspectives. This book was more social in its historical focus and I enjoyed it very much. Very rich in details and in calories! How rich Romans didn’t drop dead </span>
  <span id="freeText8109056629345387011" style="display:none">This was just the kind of historical fiction I like. In Roman historical fiction there is a glut of stories based on the army or based on Imperial or Senatorial intrigue.I’ve read quite a few of these and enjoyed them but over time I’ve found they all blend together. Either that, or many retell the same notorious events from different perspectives. This book was more social in its historical focus and I enjoyed it very much. Very rich in details and in calories! How rich Romans didn’t drop dead of heart attacks and obesity....while the details were all great, the story was more of a meander, but an interesting stroll through history I already know but from a slave’s point of view, rather like the role Tiro serves in Robert Harris’ Cicero trilogy.</span>
  <a data-text-id="8109056629345387011" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


