<div id="review_1808138770" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1808138770" />
    <a title="Alyssa Palombo" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49687552-alyssa-palombo"><img alt="Alyssa Palombo" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1562589915p2/49687552.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1808138770?book_show_action=true">Mar 09, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alyssa Palombo" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alyssa Palombo" href="/user/show/49687552-alyssa-palombo">Alyssa Palombo</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1808138770" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2556988126105153314">If you&apos;re a foodie, then this is the novel for you. Yet this book is so much more - it&apos;s a Roman epic, spanning most of the life of its hero, Thrasius, and his friends and family. You will absolutely become attached to Trasius, Aelia, Apicata, Passia, and Sotas as this novel goes on.<br/><br/>The attention to historical detail is minute and intricate, yet King has the gift of weaving in these period details seamlessly, so that the reader is never taken out of the story and feels fully immersed in the peri</span>
  <span id="freeText2556988126105153314" style="display:none">If you're a foodie, then this is the novel for you. Yet this book is so much more - it's a Roman epic, spanning most of the life of its hero, Thrasius, and his friends and family. You will absolutely become attached to Trasius, Aelia, Apicata, Passia, and Sotas as this novel goes on.<br /><br />The attention to historical detail is minute and intricate, yet King has the gift of weaving in these period details seamlessly, so that the reader is never taken out of the story and feels fully immersed in the period in all its violent, luxurious, gaudy, and bloody glory. I learned so much from reading this book while also being entertained, which to me is the sweet spot for historical fiction.<br /><br />As I discovered, the title "Feast of Sorrow" does give us some insight into events of the novel. I think this book can best be described as Game of Thrones meets the Food Network and set in Ancient Rome. Lovers of cooking, food, and historical fiction won't want to miss this book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2556988126105153314" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


