              <span id="reviewTextContainer1728043561" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16628372273155418433">Crystal King, historical fiction writer and fellow Debutante (at <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.thedebutanteball.com'>http://www.thedebutanteball.com</a>) has written an epic story of politics, romance, fabulous food, and relationships, causing the reader to be fully invested in all the people who inhabit her tale of Ancient Rome, from the slaves to the ruling class. It&apos;s a well-written book that thoroughly entertains while it also teaches about the culture, dangers, intrigues, and power plays during the reign of Augustus Caesar. Crystal has written a</span>
  <span id="freeText16628372273155418433" style="display:none">Crystal King, historical fiction writer and fellow Debutante (at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.thedebutanteball.com">http://www.thedebutanteball.com</a>) has written an epic story of politics, romance, fabulous food, and relationships, causing the reader to be fully invested in all the people who inhabit her tale of Ancient Rome, from the slaves to the ruling class. It's a well-written book that thoroughly entertains while it also teaches about the culture, dangers, intrigues, and power plays during the reign of Augustus Caesar. Crystal has written a compelling and dramatic novel in which she describes the life of Marcus Gavius Apicius, the first-ever uber-wealthy foodie, and his slave/chef Thrasius. Highly recommend!!</span>
