<span id="freeTextContainer4707605058204711939">This book is INCREDIBLE. Seriously. Set in Ancient Rome, it blends the scandals of real-life historical figures with the drama of the fictional Thrasius, a slave and companion to famed gourmand Apicius. It&apos;s clearly well-researched and richly detailed, making the story engrossing and impossible to put down. (True story: I was finishing it this morning -- Christmas morning -- and I was so reluctant to set it aside to open presents.) </span>
