        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2021707311" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2730546674806990095">I finished the audiobook for this one last night. While the narration was fine the overall plot failed to fully engage me. From a storytelling perspective, the plot feels as though it skims over the surface of what should be, or at least could be, an emotionally deeper story. Some of the problem stems from the fact that the story is being told through the perspective of Thrasius, a slave. IMO this hamstrings the plot because he can never truly react to anything going on around him because it&apos;s a</span>
  <span id="freeText2730546674806990095" style="display:none">I finished the audiobook for this one last night. While the narration was fine the overall plot failed to fully engage me. From a storytelling perspective, the plot feels as though it skims over the surface of what should be, or at least could be, an emotionally deeper story. Some of the problem stems from the fact that the story is being told through the perspective of Thrasius, a slave. IMO this hamstrings the plot because he can never truly react to anything going on around him because it's all being orchestrated by those of the upper classes. This is accurate to the time period as a slave would never be able to rebel against his master/dominus but it is very limiting. So mostly I found myself feeling emotionally unsatisfied. </span>
  <a data-text-id="2730546674806990095" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


