    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_1741988697" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1741988697" />
    <a title="Kristen McDermott" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/904982-kristen-mcdermott"><img alt="Kristen McDermott" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1455369456p2/904982.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1741988697?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristen McDermott" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristen McDermott" href="/user/show/904982-kristen-mcdermott">Kristen McDermott</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/32334413-feast-of-sorrow">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/904982-kristen-mcdermott?shelf=historical-fiction">historical-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/904982-kristen-mcdermott?shelf=2-on-kindle-read">2-on-kindle-read</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/904982-kristen-mcdermott?shelf=reviewed-books">reviewed-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/904982-kristen-mcdermott?shelf=food">food</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1741988697" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6736154070598885459">You don&apos;t have to be a foodie to enjoy this book, but if you are, you&apos;ll absolutely love it. King has created the ideal narrator to guide us through the everyday life and political turmoil of Imperial Rome in the first four decades of the Common Era. Thrasius, a slave who happens to be a culinary genius, is the talent behind the famous Roman cookbooks attributed to an author known as Apicius; King has chosen a real-life wealthy gourmand by that name to identify as the patron of those books, and </span>
  <span id="freeText6736154070598885459" style="display:none">You don't have to be a foodie to enjoy this book, but if you are, you'll absolutely love it. King has created the ideal narrator to guide us through the everyday life and political turmoil of Imperial Rome in the first four decades of the Common Era. Thrasius, a slave who happens to be a culinary genius, is the talent behind the famous Roman cookbooks attributed to an author known as Apicius; King has chosen a real-life wealthy gourmand by that name to identify as the patron of those books, and given him a complex personality and family history. By focusing on food and entertaining, King is able to depict both the glamorous lives of the rich and powerful, as well as the lives of the slaves and freedmen who made their opulent lifestyle possible, and to highlight the rituals and beliefs that guided Roman culture. Winding in and out of the streets and parlors of first-century Rome, we get a vivid sense of how much like our own time this urban metropolis was, politically and economically, but how far we've (tried to) come in terms of respect for human life and limiting our own capacity for brutality. King has also given Apicius and Thrasius complex and emotionally involving family lives, touched both by deep affection and historically-situated tragedy. My only quibble is with her occasional use of modernisms ("growing a business," for example). Otherwise, this is an absorbing, emotionally satisfying family saga.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6736154070598885459" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

