  <span id="freeText10203231669853821158" style="display:none">Crystal King's Feast of Sorrow is truly a feast. Against the backdrop of meticulously researched Ancient Rome, full of the extravagances of society at the time, brimming with incredible descriptions of true gastronomy, this is a story of a colorful cast of characters--sometimes appalling, often compelling, always richly portrayed--playing out the gamut of human behaviors and emotions. There is love, there is enmity, there is death, there is compassion, there is arrogance, there is humility, there is joy, and of course there is sorrow. And through it all there is page-turning story telling. Not to be missed.</span>
