  <span id="freeText14895387258518714399" style="display:none">Let me start by saying this is quite the impressive book. King has done her homework. Many times, I forgot I was reading a novel and thought I had picked up a memoir recovered from the first century. I found it very interesting to learn of the politics, intrigue, scheming, and happenings of ancient Rome, along with all the customs, superstitions, and loyalty to the Gods. Learning of the food during this time was also intriguing, though forgive me if flamingo tongue is not served at my next dinner party.</span>
